      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): prevent silent misparse of multi-colon delivery targets",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n`parseTelegramTarget` uses two regex parsers:\n1. `^(.+?):topic:(\\\\d+)$` — explicit `:topic:` marker (preferred)\n2. `^(.+):(\\\\d+)$` — legacy colon format for `chatId:threadId`\n\nBoth had silent misparse bugs with multi-colon targets. Malformed inputs like `chatId:topic:42:99` or `a:b:topic:42` were greedily split, embedding `:topic:N` residue in chatId.\n\n**Fix:**\n- **Topic regex**: `(.+?)` → `[^:]+` — chatId for `:topic:N` format must be colon-free\n- **Colon regex**: Keep `(.+)` + add a guard. If the left side contains unusual colons not part of a known t.me URL form, fall back to full-string instead of silently producing a wrong chatId.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n### Behavior addressed\nBefore fix:\n- `parseTelegramTarget(\\\"chatId:topic:42:99\\\")` → `chatId: \\\"chatId:topic:42\\\"`, `messageThreadId: 99` ← `:topic:42` residue in chatId\n- `parseTelegramTarget(\\\"a:b:topic:42\\\")` → `chatId: \\\"a:b:topic\\\"`, `messageThreadId: 42` ← wrong chatId\n\nAfter fix:\n- Both cases fall through to honest full-string fallback\n\n### URL-form targets preserved\n- `parseTelegramTarget(\\\"t.me/mychannel:99\\\")` → `{ chatId: \\\"t.me/mychannel\\\", messageThreadId: 99 }` ✅\n- `parseTelegramTarget(\\\"https://t.me/mychannel:77\\\")` → `{ chatId: \\\"https://t.me/mychannel\\\", messageThreadId: 77 }` ✅\n\n### Terminal output\n```\n── Bug: multi-colon misparse → full-string fallback ──\n  ✅ colon-form rejected\n  ✅ topic-embedded rejected\n  ✅ deeply nested rejected\n\n── Preserved: t.me URL-form targets with thread suffix ──\n  ✅ scheme-less t.me\n  ✅ full https URL\n\n── Regression: existing valid formats unchanged ──\n  ✅ plain numeric\n  ✅ @username\n  ✅ chatId:topic:N\n  ✅ chatId:N\n  ✅ non-numeric suffix\n  ✅ prefix stripping\n  ✅ threadId=0\n\n  12 passed, 0 failed\n```\n\n### Tests\n```bash\n$ pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/targets.test.ts\n  Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  46 passed (46)\n```\n\n### What was not tested\n- Full E2E integration with live Telegram API (requires bot token)\n\n## Tests and validation\n- `pnpm test extensions/telegram/src/targets.test.ts` — 46 passed\n- `npx oxlint` — no lint issues\n- Changes: 2 files, +38 -11\n\n## Risk checklist\n- [x] **User-facing behavior change**: No. Valid formats unchanged. Only malformed multi-colon inputs change behavior.\n- [x] **Backward compatible**: 100%. `https://t.me/...:N` targets still parse correctly.\n- [x] **Plugin SDK surface change**: No.\n- [x] **Config/doc surface change**: No.\n- [x] **New dependency**: No.\n- [x] **Both parsers (topic + colon) guarded**: Yes.",
        "branch": "fix/telegram-target-multiple-colon-misparse",
